    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-03-25T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-03-25T00:00:00-05:00" n="446"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d446">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 351.117/7.</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-03-25">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 25, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your December 27, 3 p.m., and January 16, 2 p.m. French Government advises me
                    that since Joseph Nouguier did not obtain authorization from French Government
                    to be naturalized as an American citizen in accordance with provisions of
                    Article 17, paragraph 1, of the Civil Code, French Government must continue to
                    consider him a French citizen and he must in consequence discharge his military
                    service in France.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Herrick</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
